---
title: Sync Protocol
description: WebSocket synchronization with NodeDB Origin for multi-device CRDT replication
---

# Sync Protocol

NodeDB-Lite syncs mutations to NodeDB Origin (cloud) and pulls remote changes via a custom WebSocket protocol. Synchronization is asynchronous and eventual-consistent.

## Architecture

```
┌─ NodeDB-Lite (Device 1) ──────┐
│                                │
│ CRDT State + Deltas            │
│ Memory Governor                │
│ Query Engines (HNSW, CSR)      │
│                                │
│ ┌──── Sync Task ──────────────┐│
│ │ Delta push/pull              ││
│ │ Vector clock tracking        ││
│ │ Auto-reconnect              ││
│ └──────────────────────────────┘
│       ↓ WebSocket              │
└────────┼────────────────────────┘
         │
         │ TCP + TLS
         ↓
      NodeDB Origin (Cloud)
         ↑
         │
┌────────┼────────────────────────┐
│ NodeDB-Lite (Device 2)   │      │
│                          │      │
│ CRDT State + Deltas      │      │
│ ← Deltas pulled + merged │      │
│                          │      │
└──────────────────────────┴──────┘
```

## WebSocket Protocol

5-byte frame header + payload:

```
┌─ Frame Header (5 bytes) ──────────────┐
│ msg_type (1B)   │ length (4B LE)      │
├─────────────────┼────────────────────┤
│ 0-10            │ payload bytes       │
└─────────────────┴────────────────────┘
   + Payload (JSON or binary)
```

### Message Types

| ID | Name | Direction | Purpose |
|----|----|-----------|---------|
| 0 | Handshake | C→S | Client identifies peer and peer clock |
| 1 | HandshakeAck | S→C | Server acknowledges |
| 2 | DeltaPush | C→S | Client sends pending deltas |
| 3 | DeltaAck | S→C | Server accepts deltas |
| 4 | DeltaReject | S→C | Server rejects deltas (conflict) |
| 5 | ShapeSubscribe | C→S | Subscribe to partial replication |
| 6 | ShapeSnapshot | S→C | Initial snapshot for shape |
| 7 | ShapeDelta | S→C | Incremental delta for shape |
| 8 | ShapeUnsubscribe | C→S | Unsubscribe from shape |
| 9 | VectorClockSync | S→C | Peer clock sync (periodic) |
| 10 | PingPong | C↔S | Keepalive |

## Handshake

### Client sends Handshake:

```json
{
  "peer_id": "mobile-device-01",
  "vector_clock": {
    "mobile-device-01": 42,
    "device-02": 15,
    "cloud": 100
  },
  "supported_shapes": ["Document", "Graph", "Vector"],
  "protocol_version": 1
}
```

### Server replies HandshakeAck:

```json
{
  "peer_id": "cloud",
  "vector_clock": {
    "cloud": 101,
    "mobile-device-01": 42,
    "device-02": 15
  },
  "server_time": 1679000000,
  "accepted": true
}
```

If `accepted: false`, connection closes. Reasons: invalid peer ID, protocol mismatch, rate limited.

## Delta Push

### Client sends DeltaPush:

```json
{
  "deltas": [
    {
      "id": "delta-1001",
      "peer_id": "mobile-device-01",
      "timestamp": 1679000000,
      "vector_clock": { "mobile-device-01": 43 },
      "operations": [
        {
          "type": "vector_insert",
          "collection": "embeddings",
          "doc_id": "emb-123",
          "embedding": [0.1, 0.2, 0.3],
          "metadata": null
        }
      ]
    }
  ]
}
```

### Server replies DeltaAck:

```json
{
  "acknowledged_delta_ids": ["delta-1001"],
  "server_vector_clock": { "cloud": 102 }
}
```

Client should call `acknowledge_deltas()` to clear pending buffer.

### Server sends DeltaReject on conflict:

```json
{
  "rejected_delta_id": "delta-1001",
  "reason": "UniqueViolation",
  "compensation_hint": {
    "type": "UniqueViolation",
    "field": "email",
    "existing_value": "alice@example.com",
    "details": "Document email already exists in collection"
  }
}
```

## Shape Subscriptions

Subscribe to partial replicas (fetch only matching data):

### Client sends ShapeSubscribe:

```json
{
  "shape_id": "shape-docs-2024",
  "definition": {
    "type": "Document",
    "collection": "notes",
    "predicate": { "archived": false }
  }
}
```

### Server sends ShapeSnapshot:

```json
{
  "shape_id": "shape-docs-2024",
  "snapshot": [
    {
      "id": "note-1",
      "data": { "title": "Hello", "archived": false }
    },
    {
      "id": "note-2",
      "data": { "title": "World", "archived": false }
    }
  ]
}
```

### Server sends ShapeDelta (incremental):

```json
{
  "shape_id": "shape-docs-2024",
  "delta": {
    "inserted": [
      { "id": "note-3", "data": { "title": "New", "archived": false } }
    ],
    "updated": [
      { "id": "note-1", "data": { "title": "Updated", "archived": false } }
    ],
    "deleted": ["note-2"]
  }
}
```

## Vector Clock Synchronization

Server periodically sends vector clock sync to reconcile causality:

```json
{
  "vector_clock": {
    "cloud": 105,
    "mobile-device-01": 50,
    "device-02": 25
  },
  "timestamp": 1679000010
}
```

Clients update their local vector clock to avoid stale reads.

## Reconnection and Backoff

On network failure, NodeDB-Lite retries with exponential backoff:

```
Attempt 1:  1 second
Attempt 2:  2 seconds
Attempt 3:  4 seconds
Attempt 4:  8 seconds
...
Max:       60 seconds (capped)
```

Jitter (±10%) prevents thundering herd. Connection resets backoff timer.

## Rust SDK Usage

### Enable Sync

```rust
use nodedb_lite::{NodeDbLite, SyncConfig, ShapeDefinition, ShapeType};

let db = NodeDbLite::open(&storage, "device-01").await?;

let config = SyncConfig {
    origin_url: "ws://localhost:9090".to_string(),
    shapes: vec![
        ShapeDefinition {
            id: "my-notes".to_string(),
            shape_type: ShapeType::Document {
                collection: "notes".to_string(),
                predicate: None,  // all documents
            },
        }
    ],
};

db.start_sync(config).await?;
```

### Handle Pending Deltas

```rust
// Get deltas not yet sent
let pending = db.pending_crdt_deltas().await?;
println!("Pending deltas: {}", pending.len());

// After server acks, mark as acknowledged
db.acknowledge_deltas(&[delta_id]).await?;
```

### Import Remote Deltas

```rust
// Pull remote mutations (normally done by sync task)
let remote_deltas = /* ... fetch from Origin ... */;
db.import_remote_deltas(remote_deltas).await?;
```

## Conflict Handling

When the server detects conflicts, it sends `DeltaReject` with `CompensationHint`. Applications can register handlers:

```rust
use nodedb_lite::CompensationRegistry;

let registry = CompensationRegistry::new();
registry.register("UniqueViolation", |hint| {
    println!("Unique constraint violation: {:?}", hint);
    // Return compensated delta or skip
    None
});
```

See [Compensation](./compensation.rdx) for detailed conflict resolution.

## Sync Configuration

```rust
pub struct SyncConfig {
    /// WebSocket URL (ws:// or wss://)
    pub origin_url: String,

    /// Partial replication subscriptions
    pub shapes: Vec<ShapeDefinition>,

    /// Retry backoff config (optional)
    pub max_backoff_ms: u64,      // default 60000
    pub initial_backoff_ms: u64,  // default 1000

    /// Vector clock grace period (optional)
    pub vector_clock_sync_interval_ms: u64,  // default 30000

    /// Compensation handlers (optional)
    pub compensation_registry: Option<CompensationRegistry>,
}
```

## Performance Considerations

- **Delta Batching**: Collect mutations before pushing. Batch 100 deltas → 1 WebSocket frame.
- **Shape Subscriptions**: Reduce payload by subscribing only to needed data.
- **Vector Clock**: Track causality; avoids redundant merges.
- **Reconnection**: Exponential backoff prevents server overload during outages.
- **Memory**: Pending deltas buffered in memory; large batches may require `flush()` to disk.

## Error Handling

Sync task runs in background. Handle errors via callback:

```rust
db.start_sync(config).await?;

// Later: check sync status (pseudo-code)
let status = db.sync_status().await?;
if !status.connected {
    eprintln!("Sync disconnected: {}", status.error);
}
```

